sec.p:
Association analyses of whole-genome SNP genotypes, together with the previously identified SNPs ELOVL6:c.-533C > T, ELOVL6:c.-480C > T, ELOVL6:c.416C > T [2] and the newly detected ELOVL6:c.1408A > G and ELOVL6:c.1922C > T SNPs were performed on the following phenotypes: RT-qPCR expression data of ELOVL6 mRNA in backfat and C16:0 and C16:1(n-7) fatty acids composition in backfat and intramuscular fat. The position of the SNPs was based on the Sscrofa10.2 genome assembly [http://www.animalgenome.org/repository/pig/]. GWAS were performed with a mixed model [31,32] that accounted for additive effects associated with each marker (see below) by using the Qxpak 5.0 software [33]:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}				\usepackage{amsmath}
